<DOC><DOCNO> AP880322-0312 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-22-88 1840EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f AM-CSX-TotalMinatome     03-22 0172</FIRST><SECOND>AM-CSX-Total Minatome,0178</SECOND><HEAD>CSX to Sell Oil and Gas Unit to Total Minatome</HEAD><DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   CSX Corp. said Tuesday it has agreed tosell its oil and natural gas exploration subsidiary toHouston-based Total Minatome Corp. for $612 million.   The sale of CSX Oil andamp; Gas Corp. is expected to be completed inabout 30 days, said CSX Chairman Hays T. Watkins in a jointannouncement with Minatome President Jean-Pierre Donnet.   The CSX subsidiary's principal operations are located in theUnited States, mostly along the Gulf coasts of Texas and Louisiana,and in the North Sea.   Total Minatome is involved in exploration and production inWyoming, Oklahoma, the Gulf Coast and the Gulf of Mexico. It is awholly-owned subsidiary of Total Compagnie Francaise des Petroles,which is based in France.   The deal will allow Total Minatome a chance to expand its U.S.and North Sea operations and is in keeping with CSX's plan toconcentrate on its primary transportation, pipeline, property andtechnology groups, Donnet and Watkins said.</TEXT></DOC>